reviews.review_text:
DS Jam > LIG Jam > Slipknot! Jam > Stella Blue Guys, guys, guys, I've been reading all the other reviews, and no one is giving a detailed synopsis of this top ten Dark Star (albeit without the first or second verse). Good god, what an experience!!!  This second set run is absolutely phenomenal. And nobody comments on the spacey Let It Grow Jam between the DS Jam and the Slipknot! Jam?  Am I missing something here? I think knot!

Boy oh boy, I never could have imagined falling onto this  purely by accident with nary a hint from anyone in the community praising this 32:52 minute sleeper to the high heavens?

And this version is wayyyy down on the list of favorites in Headyversions with only 27 votes (as of this review).  That is outrageous!? That is a crime. 

This is what Grendel said about it in Headyversions - "Where has this one been hiding?  Jazz chops galore for the first half into some gorgeous, quiet, drifting space & then a collective color palette of mid 70s fusion stuff that's unique to most Dark Stars I've heard. Never gets dissonant or screechy...and not a word is sung...a completely instrumental Dark Star in the best possible way...oh, and uh, yeah there's that whole Slipknot! Jam thing ya get too." 

Get it folks. Definitely a five star MUST HAVE for the collection! 

BTW, I chose to ditch JBG and OMSN in favor of a super beautiful and completely unique listening experience with this rundown --  DS Jam > LIG Jam > Slipknot! Jam > Stella Blue > UJB > U.S. Blues > Ship Of Fools. It's why we fell in love with the band oh-so-long ago.
